description: Borrowed from New Latin subclavius, from sub- (“under”) +‎ clavicula (“collar bone, clavicle”) +‎ -ius (suffix to form an adjective).

entries.meaning: (anatomy) A muscle which (in humans) originates from the first costal cartilage and inserts on to the undersurface of the clavicle, acting to elevate the first rib or fix the clavicle.
